content.text: I can see the issue. The script is trying to use perlbrew with Perl 5.40.0, but there are module installation failures. Let me try a simpler approach by using the system Perl and checking if the basic Catalyst modules are available. First, let me check what Perl modules are already available in the system:

content.text: The issue is that the basic Perl modules like Moose are not installed. Let me install the essential system packages first:

content.command: sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y libmoose-perl libcatalyst-perl libcatalyst-modules-perl libdbix-class-perl libtemplate-perl
